  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with complex legal frameworks designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute such activities. Here's an overview of the key legal aspects:\n\n1. International Legal Frameworks\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- Basel Committee Guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Act\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n3. Core Legal Requirements\n- Customer Due Diligence (CDD)\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping regulations\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n5. Regulatory Compliance\n- Financial institutions must implement robust AML programs\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Staff training\n- Internal control mechanisms\n\n6. International Cooperation\n- Cross-border information sharing\n- Extradition agreements\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent financial crimes and track potential illicit financial activities.",
